President Obama will meet with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg on April 4, 2016, to discuss various issues. The President will express solidarity with NATO following the recent terrorist attacks in Brussels. They will also discuss progress in the fight against ISIL and NATO's role in addressing the refugee crisis caused by the group. Additionally, preparations for the upcoming NATO Summit in Warsaw will be discussed, including efforts to reinforce deterrence in Europe and address instability in the region. The visit highlights the importance of the transatlantic bond and the need for NATO to adapt to a changing strategic environment.